iences with nature, Krall provides a critical focus and a timely contribution to the current debate surrounding our relationship to land and nature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aLand reformzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aLand use, RuralzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aPublic landszUnited StatesxHistory. 4aBusiness and Economics : Economic History. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aHistory : American History. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438430805423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438430805/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles